- id: '2069214731043217762'
  text: 'Ever have a problem with @Spotify just randomly stopping playback, or not
    automatically going to the next track?  I have...


    I had tried everything, systematically to hunt down the issue, and I think I found
    it.


    After having turned off everything I could think of, canvas, gapless playback,
    lower resolution playback... nothing seemed to work.  I would stare at the screen
    just watching playback stop at approximately 2 seconds before the track would
    end, and then start, and then stop at the end of the track...


    This happened with just about everything from Filter to Billy Eilish, but it didn''t
    happen with a lot of things which kind of confused me.  Some playlists, mostly
    instrumental ones played back just fine, unless there were parts in which there
    was a vocalist...


    Then I noticed the lyrics.  Lyrics are presented in one of two ways:  Sync''d
    with the music, and just simply being there... And so I wondered... "Where does
    Spotify  get it''s lyrics from?  Surely there it has it''s own database...".  I
    was mistaken.  Spotify does not actually have a database of lyrics, and uses third
    party sites and databases, and as far as I can tell, not just one.


    It would appear that the main culprit was the Lyric / Audio Syncing Feature.  I''m
    guessing that Spotify makes a type of request back and forth with almost every
    track, looking for Lyrics and it has to wait for a response from whomever, which
    is causing the seemingly random playback stopping.


    So, the solution to the problem?  Turn off lyrics and lyrical display, and you
    should get seemless playback, and no stoppage.'
